PNo1: Smart Campus Life & Occupancy Management System
Goal: A platform that monitors how crowded campus facilities are (library, cafeteria, study
rooms, event halls) and lets students reserve time slots when needed.
Who uses it? Students, campus staff, event organizers.
Typical flow:
• A student checks: “Is the library crowded right now?”
• If it’s full, the system suggests alternative facilities.
• For reservable spaces (study rooms, halls), students book hour-based time slots.
• “Sensor data” can be simulated (e.g., occupancy count updated every minute).
Database should store:
• Facilities (name, location, capacity)
• Live occupancy logs (timestamp, current count)
• Reservations (student, facility, start/end time, status)
Interface should include:
• A dashboard “heat map” of crowded areas
• A calendar view for bookings (day/hour)
• A student profile page (“My reservations”, cancel/edit)

